OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1775304668
OL,3,CUnion says more strikes at Greater
OL,4,CManchester hospitals in overtime row
OL,6,FThe union Unison says the Northern
OL,7,FCare Alliance strike will be the
OL,8,Fsecond in an ongoing dispute over
OL,9,Fovertime payments. Talks aimed at
OL,10,Faverting walkouts collapsed last month.
OL,12,FThe row centres on the trust's use of
OL,13,Fan outside agency to manage overtime.
OL,14,FThe union says staff are paid less
OL,15,Fthan directly employed NHS workers who
OL,16,Fdo overtime, and they miss out on
OL,17,Fpension contributions.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,398,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1775304668
OL,3,CUnion says more strikes at Greater
OL,4,CManchester hospitals in overtime row
OL,6,FUnison's North West regional organiser
OL,7,FKevin Dolan said: "It's disappointing
OL,8,Fthe trust has ignored the union's
OL,9,Frequests to sit down and negotiate a
OL,10,Fresolution to this dispute.
OL,12,F"Nobody wants to be on strike and
OL,13,Fthere's still time for managers to
OL,14,Fcome back with a fair solution and
OL,15,Favoid disruption.
OL,17,F"But cutting pay and slashing pensions
OL,18,Fis no way to deal with staff
OL,19,Fshortages. Many workers are already
OL,20,Fstruggling to make ends meet and are
OL,21,Frightly angry at this approach."
OL,26,@oD@SOUtD@AOUyD@AOU}D@`O]
